    It generates a list of prime numbers less than or equal to 'n', 
    then iterates over each number in 'lst', calculates its absolute value,

    """

    result = 1
    for num in lst:
        value = abs(num)
        if value != 0 and all((value % p != 0 for p in primes)):
            result *= value
